INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_alh4300','letter','1783-03-17','Philadelphia','PA','US','Alexander Hamilton','','','George','Washington','','individual','','Our affairs wear a most serious aspect, as well foreign as domestic. Before this gets to hand, your Excellency will probably have seen the Provisional Articles between Great Britain and these States.','ltr_alh4300.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume IV., Jared Sparks, 1853');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_alh4301','letter','1783-03-25','Philadelphia','PA','US','Alexander Hamilton','','','George','Washington','','individual','','The army, by their resolutions, express an expectation that Congress will not disband them previous to a settlement of accounts, and the establishment of funds. Congress may resolve upon the first, but the General opinion is that they cannot constitutionally declare the second.','ltr_alh4301.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume IV., Jared Sparks, 1853');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_alh4302','letter','1783-03-25','Philadelphia','PA','US','Alexander Hamilton','','','George','Washington','','individual','','Here I write as a citizen zealous for the true happiness of this country; as a soldier, who feels what is due to an army which has suffered every thing, and done much for the safety of America.','ltr_alh4302.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume IV., Jared Sparks, 1853');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_alh4303','letter','1783-04-11','','','US','Alexander Hamilton','','','George','Washington','','individual','','The idea of not attempting to separate the army before the settlement of accounts, corresponds with my proposition. That of endeavouring to let them have some pay, has also appeared to me indispensable.','ltr_alh4303.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume IV., Jared Sparks, 1853');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_alh4304','letter','1783-04-15','Philadelphia','PA','US','Alexander Hamilton','','','George','Washington','','There are two resolutions passed, relative to the restoration of the British prisoners, and to making arrangements for the surrender of the posts in the possession of the British troops','','description','ltr_alh4304.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume IV., Jared Sparks, 1853');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_alh4305','letter','1785-11-23','','','US','Alexander Hamilton','','','George','Washington','','individual','','The Society of this State met some short time since, and took into consideration the proposed alterations in the original frame of the Institution. Some were strenuous for adhering to the old Constitution, a few for adopting the new, and many for a middle line.','ltr_alh4305.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume IV., Jared Sparks, 1853');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_alh4306','letter','1787-07-03','New York','NY','US','Alexander Hamilton','','','George','Washington','','individual','','The prevailing apprehension among thinking men is, that the Convention, from the fear of shocking the popular opinion, will not go far enough. They seem to be convinced, that a strong, well-mounted Government, will better suit the popular palate, than one of a different complexion.','ltr_alh4306.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume IV., Jared Sparks, 1853');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_alh4307','letter','1787-10-30','','','US','Alexander Hamilton','','','George','Washington','','individual','','I am much obliged to your Excellency for the explicit manner in which you contradict the insinuations mentioned in my last letter. The only use I shall make of your answer, will he to put it into the hands of a few friends.','ltr_alh4307.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume IV., Jared Sparks, 1853');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_alh4308','letter','1790-10-17','New York','NY','US','Alexander Hamilton','','','George','Washington','','individual','','A British packet arrived yesterday. The accounts she brings are all of a warlike aspect.','ltr_alh4308.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume IV., Jared Sparks, 1853');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_alh4309','letter','1791-04-10','Philadelphia','PA','US','Alexander Hamilton','','','George','Washington','','individual','','It is to be lamented that our system is such as still to leave the public peace of the Union at the mercy of each State Government.','ltr_alh4309.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume IV., Jared Sparks, 1853');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_alh4310','letter','1791-09-22','Philadelphia','PA','US','Alexander Hamilton','','','George','Washington','','individual','','I have received a letter from the Minister of France, of which the inclosed is a copy.','ltr_alh4310.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume IV., Jared Sparks, 1853');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_alh4311','letter','1792-08-18','Philadelphia','PA','US','Alexander Hamilton','','','George','Washington','','individual','','I am happy to be able, at length, to send you answers to the objections which were communicated in your letter of the 29th of July.','ltr_alh4311.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume IV., Jared Sparks, 1853');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_alh4312','letter','1792-11-19','Philadelphia','PA','US','Alexander Hamilton','','','George','Washington','','individual','','I have carefully reflected on the application of Mr. Ternant, for an additional supply of money for the use of the Colony of St. Domingo, on account of the debt due to France, which I regard more and more as presenting a subject extremely delicate and embarrassing.','ltr_alh4312.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume IV., Jared Sparks, 1853');
